casebody.data:
Wells, Respondent, v. Genin, Appellant. (City Court of New York, General Term. November 25, 1892.) Action by Oliver J. Wells against Frank B. Benin. Judgment for plaintiff. Defendant appeals. Affirmed.

Argued before Newburger and Fitzsimons, JJ.

Culver & Anthony, for appellant. Wells & Waldo, for respondent. Newburger, J.

This is an appeal from a judgment entered upon the verdict of a jury. The case was properly submitted to the jury, and, as there are no exceptions in the case that deserve serious consideration, the judgment appealed from must be affirmed, with costs.
